{"key":"post-7188948","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7188948</id>\n<content>The 'casing' is the non-nutritious layer on top.  The word is often used incorrectly here and repeated endlessly.  I've almost given up on trying to correct people for the misused terms.  'Casing' is not a term to use for a project.  The casing is the layer placed over the substrate to provide moisture and a suitable microclimate for fruiting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's very important for people to use the correct nomenclature on a site that dispenses information.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7188953</next>\n<prev>7188914</prev>\n<first>7188905</first>\n<last>7189910</last>\n<when>1184711966</when>\n<utime>07/18/07 01:39 AM</utime>\n</post>"}